Coding Principles
- Declare variables at the lowest possible scope
- Check the type of the value returned from a function
- A function should accomplish one and only one objective
- Achieve x% code coverage
- Naming conventions
    - filters: object containing search parameters
    - options: object containing runtime configuration options
- Use backticks for strings
- Expose Controllers via an abstract object
- 'createResource' use cases are how canonical objects get created and values get validated

